OL,3,CMan found guilty of manslaughter after
OL,4,CEllesmere Port stabbing
OL,6,F"Everyone who mourns Lloyd knew him
OL,7,Fand loved him. Yet, his son will never
OL,8,Fhave the opportunity to meet and get
OL,9,Fto know his dad, something no child
OL,10,Fshould have to endure. And from
OL,11,FLloyd's baby's point of view, justice
OL,12,Fwill never be served.
OL,14,F"Lloyd is not able to speak for
OL,15,Fhimself, and sadly two lives have been
OL,16,Fruined as the result of Ben Ruddock's
OL,17,Fhorrific actions."
