OL,3,CMan found guilty of manslaughter after
OL,4,CEllesmere Port stabbing
OL,6,FOn the night of the stabbing, Lloyd
OL,7,Fand a female friend of his attended
OL,8,FRuddock's home address to collect an e-
OL,9,Fbike which they believed had been
OL,10,Fstolen from an associate. There was a
OL,11,Fminor altercation between Lloyd and
OL,12,FRuddock. The e-bike was recovered, and
OL,13,FLloyd and his friend left the address.
OL,15,FRuddock then sent multiple threatening
OL,16,Fvoice notes to the woman's phone,
OL,17,Fdirected towards Lloyd. Ruddock armed
OL,18,Fhimself with a knife from a barbecue
OL,19,Fset and told Lloyd to meet him at a
OL,20,Fpark.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
