OL,3,CMan found guilty of manslaughter after
OL,4,CEllesmere Port stabbing
OL,6,F"While no conviction is going to bring
OL,7,FLloyd back to his family and friends,
OL,8,FI hope the conclusion of this trial
OL,9,Fwill help to bring them some closure,
OL,10,Fknowing that the person responsible
OL,11,Ffor his death has been held
OL,12,Faccountable for his actions.
OL,14,F"What happened on the evening of 1 May
OL,15,F2024 was entirely avoidable. Ruddock
OL,16,Fchose to arm himself with a knife and
OL,17,Fmade continued threats towards Lloyd.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
